trative support  laboratory  maintenance  accounting and billing coding Extra Help  temporary Civil Service employees  thereby allowing medical students to practice physical exams  history taking and communication skills in the medical field  This experience gives students an opportunity to learn and to be evaluated on learned skills in a simulated clinical environment Application Process Faculty  Follow application link on online posting Apply online at jobs uic edu  questions should be referred to UIC Help Desk at                 Human Resources will review your qualifications and  if qualified  contact you to schedule an examination jobs uic edu  Please note that your qualifications for Civil Service examinations are determined based on application materials  a detailed resume  copy of your college university transcripts  and DD     if applicable  must be received in Human Resources by the closing date of the job  the names of the top three candidates will be referred to the department for interviews Apply online at jobs uic edu  questions should be referred to UIC Help Desk at                 E mail rockfordhr uic edu to express interest in a particular extra help job jobs uic edu rockfordhr uic edu The Office of Medical Education and Evaluation at the College of Medicine Rockford hires Extra Help employees who work with medical students to complete clinical skills assessments  We are recruiting individuals who can communicate effectively and be available for varied daytime hours to be Standardized Patients  For more information and to ensure your application is directed appropriately  contact the office at seemac uic edu seemac uic edu Standardized Patient Job Description Standardized Patient  Current Vacancies click here About Welcome From Regional Dean UIC Health Sciences Campus Rockford Fast Facts More About the Region Visiting the Campus Employment Contact Us About Education Research Patient Care Departments News Giving INFORMATION FOR  Prospective and Curr